### Content Approach (Competitors)
Competitors deliver workmanlike step lists with minimal warmth or real-world context. Most go straight into steps without diagnosing why beginners fail first. None build in a "nail health readiness" check before you even pick up the file. Visual guides are utilitarian; no one speaks to the asymmetry anxiety that beginners report as their number-one frustration. Nearly all miss the nuance between shaping natural nails vs enhancements.

### Our Strategic Approach

**Differentiation:** Lead with the reader's actual fear — "I always end up with one nail looking totally different from the others" — before a single step is given. Competitors skip this emotional reality. Mirellé addresses it head-on, then teaches the centre-mark trick and the alternating-strokes method to fix it permanently. The result: a tutorial that feels like it knows you, not just a numbered list.

**Structure plan:** Open with a nail health / readiness check (unique section — no competitor has this), move into a gear guide framed by grit, then into the step tutorial with branching notes for natural vs extension nails. Close with maintenance that feeds into seasonal redesigns and links to inspiration posts.

**Tone direction:** Warm, confident friend who happens to be a nail technician — not a clinical manual. British English. Practical, precise, encouraging.

