## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

| Field | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| Recommended Voice | Confident, warm nail-savvy friend — someone who has made every mistake herself and now knows exactly how to help you avoid them |
| Tone Characteristics | Direct and precise without being clinical; uses "you" throughout; names the reader's anxiety before solving it; light wit but never flippant on technique; reassuring on short nails / beginner status |
| Language Style | British English. Short sentences for steps. Longer sentences for context/explanation. No jargon without definition. Use "file" not "emery," "sidewalls" not "lateral edges." Avoid the word "straightforward." No em dashes. |
| Audience Match | Readers are 18–35, self-sufficient, used to DIY beauty content on TikTok and YouTube. They expect actionable specificity. Generic encouragement ("you've got this!") lands flat. Concrete micro-tips ("after 3 strokes on the left, switch to the right") earn trust. |

